column4: Batting - Park Adjusted Runs Above Average based on wOBA
column5: Base Running - Base running runs above average, includes SB or CS
column6: Fielding - Fielding Runs Above Average based on UZR (TZ before 2002)
column7: Positional - Positional Adjustment set at +12.5 for C, +7.5 for SS, +2.5 for 2B/3B/CF, -7.5 for RF/LF, -12.5 for 1B, -17.5 for DH
column9: Offense - Batting and Base Running combined (above average)
column10: Defense - Fielding and Positional Adjustment combined (above average)
column12: League - League adjustment to zero out wins above average
column13: Replacement - Replacement Runs set at 20 runs per 600 plate apperances
column15: RAR - Runs Above Replacement (Batting + Fielding + Base Running + Replacement + Positional)
column17: Dollars - WAR converted to a dollar scale based on what a player would make in free agency
